headline: Eni and Petronas Forge Major Southeast Asia Upstream Joint Venture
summary: Eni and Petronas have formed an equally-owned joint venture to combine their upstream assets in Indonesia and Malaysia, planning a $15 billion investment over five years to develop 3 billion barrels of oil equivalent and target 10 billion boe of unrisked exploration potential.
